              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#37437B" valign="top" width="100" nowrap><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2"><b>Bonesmash</b></font></td>
                <td bgcolor="#37437B" valign="top" width="100%"><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;01/26/2004&nbsp;: 1:14:37 PM</small><hr size="1"><span class="spnMessageText"> <i>My mind seethes. Anger....Anger...Must control the anger... must... must... </i><br /><br />I had awoke this morning to go to a place I had recently discovered. I had found a group of creatures which did not assist nor care about each other (either due to divine intervention or a defective birth process, I care not why.) <br /><br />It was so easy - I could read "The Cabilis Daily" and still keep killing with impunity. <br /><br />However - as I sat there - a wee doggie began to run around my ankles. <br /><br />"This is camped!" It said. <br />How sweet! A talking pooch! <br /><br />A HUGE bear ambled over to the dog and I. <br />"Yeah, Bro - this is camped - I'm Power leveling this druid here. Get out." <br /><br />All these human phrases.. Bro? Power Leveling? Ah! He must mean the act of training a young one at an accelerated pace. My master told me of these things. <br /><br />But - I digress. <br /><br />I said nary a word, but as the brute spawned, I told my helper to engage and threw on three of my most tasty Damage over time spells. <br /><br />BOOM! It was dead. <br /><br />Hey! You can'...... <br /><br />Boom. Another one dead. <br /><br />I'm gonna repor.... <br />BOOM - Dead. <br /><br />"You wait right here, buddy. You are in SO much trouble." <br />I waited for a magical holding spell to make me "wait right here." However, none ever came. <br /><br />I shambled off, found more creatures and took them down - barely pausing in my stride. <br /><br />Eventually a knight in shining armor appeared before me. <br />"Hail, Bonesmasher." <br /><br />"Hello, IamLeetsmoothie." <br /><br />"Bonesmasher, you must share the camp." <br /><br />My response? "What camp? "Who else is here? <br /><br />His response - "Yonder camp - you must share it." <br /><br />My response - "I am fighting here. I am not fighting over there." <br /><br />His response - "Well, if you do fight over there - then share." <br /><br />After IamLeetsmoothie had left I walked back over the where the doggie and his buddy Bear were.I informed them that their pleas had been answered, a knight had told me I must share. <br /><br />They laughed and pointed and laughed again. <br /><br />They were still laughing when my charmed undead Giant skeleton ambled up by my side. <br />He had brought a few friends - who were none too pleased I had charmed their friend. <br /><br />"Here guys, I brought some more to share!" I said as I cast my gate spell. <br /><br />Ever seen a doggie turned inside out? Quite intriguing, actually. <br /><br /><i>Every victory is sweet - but to kill the arrogant, - OH! That is honey to the mouth!</i></span></font></td>
              </tr>
